Description.Text: This hotel makes an excellent choice for all types of travellers, particularly those who want to experience the bustle of central London first hand. (11/07LP)
This hotel is centrally located dominating the Strand in the heart of Theatreland and just five minutes from Covent Garden, Trafalgar Square and Charing Cross mainline and underground stations.

Club rooms offer better facilities and amenities than standard rooms. These include robes, mineral water and state of the art TV system providing blockbuster movies and audio CDs on demand, broadband Internet access plus Wi-Fi capabilities. As this hotel is so large, guests will find a floor plan when they exit the lifts to help them find their room.
It is a vast Edwardian building in traditional style for its era, and very imposing from the outside.
The hotel's main restaurant is decorated in a modern style with attractive light wood furnishings. The hotel also offers a bar and a juice bar.
The lobby is very large, offering a number of shops and plentiful seating.
